This paper discusses privacy concerns in collaborative intrusion detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of cryptographic technologies, which is a subfield of cryptography and security (cs.CY). The topic of threat intelligence and global context of attacks is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the architecture for collaborative intrusion detection, which can be related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and system and information theory (cs.SI).
